<subSubSection id="FC8E653B875FB1051E0954B0F867FCC7" pageId="16" pageNumber="209" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875FB1051E0954B0F867FCC7" blockId="16.[1356,2566,280,908]" pageId="16" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="86E0EAA2875FB1051E0954B0F927FD3E" bold="true" box="[1360,1715,674,707]" pageId="16" pageNumber="209">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. No specimens of the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875FB1051DF854D8F96FFD16" authorityName="Rhoads" authorityYear="1894" box="[1697,1787,714,747]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="209" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alticola">alticola</taxonomicName>
have been collected since 1934, and it may be extinct. The other subspecies (inexpectatus) has been verified since 1978 at three localities, and it may be present at several other historical sites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
